          <li>based on the maximum soil carbon content of 190 Mg/ha and a 10% increase from fertilizer, the maximum biomass yield of corn is 16.7619 Mg/Ha</li>
          <li>50% of the corn biomass is considered kernel, and 50% stover
            <ul>
