        <strong>Prices</strong><br />
        <br />
        By default prices are fixed at $150 per ton for switchgrass and $250 for corn and do not change over the course of the game. The dynamic economy can be turned on by selecting the &quot;Market-driven prices&quot; option on the moderator screen, which will allow prices to change from year to year.<br />
        <br />
        Prices are computed according to a simple model designed to represent the basic dynamics of supply and demand and to add an additional dimension for players to compete on. The market demands a certain amount of each crop, currently fixed at 60% of fields for corn and 40% for grass. This is matched with the number of tons of each crop supplied by the farmers, and prices are adjusted according the the discrepancy. The adjustment is dampened by a stickiness factor, currently fixed and 0.3, so prices will never change by more than 30% of their previous value in one year.<br />
